		(property "Description" "P4 isolation PhotoMOS (1-Form-B NC): bridges raw P4 to K5_LATCH at rest and without board power. Once K5's auxiliary contact proves the relay has pulled in, P4_ISO energises K6 through the direct K6_RET-to-K5 auxiliary-contact return, opening that bridge while K5 remains sealed from P2. Loss of K5 interrupts the operating return and restores the normally-closed P4 path; R35 and R44 keep GPIO4 sensing from becoming an alternate operating return."
			(at 0 0 0)
			(layer "F.Fab")
			(hide yes)
